multipleChoice.question:
What is printed?
int a = 5, b = 2;
System.out.println(a / b + a % b);

What is the final value of x?
int x = 10;
x = x++ + ++x;

What prints?
int m = 7;
System.out.println(m > 5 && m < 10);

What is x?
int x = 4;
x *= 3 + 2;

What is printed?
int a = 10;
System.out.println(a == 10 || a / 0 == 2);

What is printed?
int n = 5;
System.out.println(n++ + ++n);

What prints?
int a = 3, b = 4;
System.out.println(a > b ? a : b);

What is printed?
int x = 4;
System.out.println(++x * 2);

Evaluate:
int x = 5;
x += x * 2;

What prints?
int a = 2, b = 3, c = 4;
System.out.println(a + b * c - a);

What is printed?
boolean flag = false;
System.out.println(!flag || true);

What prints?
int x = 1;
x = x + x++ + ++x;

What is printed?
int x = 10;
System.out.println(x-- - --x);

What prints?
int a = 8, b = 3;
System.out.println((a / b) * b);

What prints?
int a = 6;
a /= 2;
a -= 1;
System.out.println(a);

What is printed?
int a = 5, b = 10;
System.out.println((a > b) ? a + b : a * b);
